content.description:
This short four bolt route is more like a tall V5.  It's almost awesome that it is documented in several locations only as "Unnamed 11a".  This may have, at one time, been the cliff warm-up, but don't expect 11a difficulty here.

 The route consists of long moves on pockets and edges with the difficulty easing off at the last bolt and chains as you climb a very cool dike feature.
content.location: This one it easy to pass as you hike along the wall if you aren't looking.  Try to spot the very low set of chains and the beginning of the route which is located in a nice little cove with orange pocketed rock.

content.description: South-east facing, leftmost area of The Farmhouse. Great rock with great potential, but get lots of sun exposure all day long.
